---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use • Fin Sanctuary"
  description="Read the Fin Sanctuary terms of use covering educational content, external links, accuracy limits, and use of the site."
>
  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-primary/10 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(1,133,174,0.08),rgba(243,239,238,0.55))] dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(13,175,188,0.14),rgba(2,6,23,0.95))]">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10 md:py-12">
        <div class="text-[0.72rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-primary/75">Terms of Use</div>
        <h1 class="mt-5 font-bold tracking-tight text-primary">The practical rules for using Fin Sanctuary.</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200">
          Fin Sanctuary is designed as an educational and planning resource for home and small-office aquarium owners. By using the site, you agree to use the content responsibly and understand its practical limits.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10">
      <article class="rounded-[2rem] border border-primary/10 bg-white px-7 py-8 shadow-[0_24px_80px_-55px_rgba(1,133,174,0.42)] dark:border-white/8 dark:bg-slate-900 md:px-9">
        <div class="space-y-7 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Educational Use Only</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">The content on Fin Sanctuary is intended to help readers make better aquarium decisions, but it is educational in nature. It is not veterinary advice, medical advice, legal advice, or a guarantee that a specific setup, fish choice, or product will succeed in every situation.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">No Professional Guarantee</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Aquarium care depends on individual tank conditions, water chemistry, livestock health, maintenance habits, and local circumstances. Readers remain responsible for their own tank decisions, animal welfare, and purchasing choices.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Accuracy and Updates</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Fin Sanctuary aims to provide practical and accurate guidance, but product availability, compatibility information, pricing, and care recommendations can change over time. Content may be updated as new information or new site features are added.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">External Links and Third Parties</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">The site may link to YouTube, storefronts, affiliate offers, or other third-party resources. Fin Sanctuary is not responsible for third-party content, availability, checkout flow, or policies on those external services.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Product and Fit Responsibility</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Any 3D-printed accessory, affiliate-linked item, or recommended product should be reviewed for fit and suitability before use. Buyers remain responsible for confirming dimensions, compatibility, and safe use in their own tanks.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Site Changes</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Fin Sanctuary may change, update, remove, or expand site features, content, products, guides, videos, and contact options without prior notice.</p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
